<section class="content">
  <div class="col-1">
    <h2>Engagement Length</h2>
  </div>

  <div class="col-2">
    <p>If this is our first time working together I ask for a sixth month commitment to begin. This includes 60 minute bi-weekly sessions, email and text support, 30 minute “spot” coaching as needed, and my session notes (people often share that even years after our work has ended they still find great value in the notes). Typically folks work with me for around 12 - 24 months.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<hr />

<section class="content">
  <div class="col-1">
    <h2>Confidentiality</h2>
  </div>

  <div class="col-2">
    <p>I do my best to practice good data hygiene to ensure privacy and confidentiality: </p>
    <ul class="bullets">
      <li>Anything discussed in session is completely confidential. If we are working with support from your boss/investors/board, I will not share anything from our work together without your consent.</li>
      <li>I like to record intake sessions just in case I need to reference something when drafting the structure of the coaching program. I record directly to my computer and once I have shared the program with you I permanantely delete the file.</li>
      <li>Similarly, should you choose to record your sessions, they will be stored locally on your computer (basically I avoid all contact with the cloud).
      <li>AI does not touch any part of our engagement, at least from my end 🤫.</li>
      <li>During our session I will take notes with pen and paper, which are then transcribed into “process notes” (these are notes I take for myself after each session) afterwards.
      <li>I write my process notes in a local Obsidian vault that is backed up to a hard drive, not to the cloud. These notes are anonymized and scrubbed of any Personally Identifiable Information.</li>
      <li>I <em>do</em> send session notes via email (to the address of your choosing). Should you prefer me to share notes in your system of choice (Notion, Google Docs, etc.) I am happy to do that as well.
      <li>Once we have completed our work together, I will keep my process notes for up to one year, at which point I will permanently delete them.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<hr />

<section class="content">
  <div class="col-1">
    <h2>Price & Billing</h2>
  </div>

  <div class="col-2">
    <p>I use a “pay from the heart” pricing model in my practice. This isn't “pay what you want” or a sliding scale, but rather an invitation for you to connect with your heart and find a price that feels right for the work we do together. A price that honors your commitment and mine, and one that very importantly doesn't break the bank. The suggested range I work within is $7200 to $15400 USD for a six month engagement with 60 minute bi-weekly sessions. I can invoice everything up front or bill on a quarterly or monthly cadence.</p>

    <p>Reduced rates are available for folks in non-profits and government services, as well as a limited number of "low bono" slots for those facing financial hardship.</p>

    <p>While credit cards can be accomodated, ACH is much preferred.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<hr />

<section class="content">
  <div class="col-1">
    <h2>Single Session Alternative</h2>
  </div>

  <div class="col-2">
    <p>For some folks, a six month engagement isn’t what is needed.</p>

    <p>If you have a particular issue, challenge, or opportunity you’d like coaching on, I offer a single session, two hour deep-dive on a topic of your choosing.</p>

    <p>I’ll send you a kickoff questionairre to fill out with as much information as you can, and then we’ll meet for an in-depth coaching session. Afterwards you’ll receive a recording of the video, additional resources, and a set of action items to move forward with.</p>

    <p>The cost is $750 - $1,250 USD for this session.</p>
  </div>
</section>

